1.Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart; 
2.Start kicking your feet up until the heel touches the glutes; 
3.Pump your arms at the same time.

1.Stand with your feet hip-width apart; 
2.Drive the right knee up to meet your left elbow; 
3.Immediately repeat with the left knee meeting your right elbow.

1.Stand with your feet together; 
2.jump up with your legs spread wider than hip width apart while raising arms above your head; 
3.Quickly reverse and repeat.

1.Start with wide step-and-touch; 
2.lean down to the side with an arm straight and the other arm bent; 
3.Alternate while stepping side to side.

1.Start lying down on a mat; 
2.Move your legs in a bicycle motion several inches off the floor; 
3.Keep your arms extended and your chest open.

1.Sit with your knees bent, hands on your knees; 
2.Lean back slightly with your arms extended; 
3.Straighten and raise your legs toward the ceiling until your body forms a V shape. Hold the position.

1.Start off with a plank position; 
2.Rock forward on your toes until your chin is over your fingertips; 
3.Hold for a second before returning to the start position.

1.Lie on back with knees bent and feet on floor; 
2.Raise hips by pressing weight into heels; 
3.Lower back to the start position.

1.Stand and squat down with your hands on the floor; 
2.Then jump your feet back into a plank position; 
3.Do one basic push-up, jump the feet forward and back into a squat; 
4.Explode to a jump and land softly.

1.Start off a plank position; 
2.Reach and tap your foot with your opposite hand; 
3.Pull your knee to your shoulder; 
4.reverse the movement and repeat.

1.Start face down on the floor resting on your forearms and knees; 
2.Push off the floor with your elbows, raising up off your knees onto your toes; 
3.Hold the position.

1.Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart; 
2.Step one leg out, bend the other knee until it nearly touches the floor; 
3.Return to the start position; 
4.Reverse and repeat.

1.Lie on your back with your knees bent at 90 degrees; 
2.Raise your arms straight overhead, pointing up throughout the exercise;
3.Sit up halfway, then return to the floor.

1.Stand with hands raised to hip height; 
2.Run in place while lifting your knees as high as possible; 
3.Pump your arms at the same time.

1.Start by standing with your feet hip-width apart; 
2.Bend forward to place your hands on the mat, walk your hands out all the way into a full plank position; 
3.Hold for seconds, walk your hands back and roll up to standing.

1.Place your hands on a surface shoulder width apart; 
2.Step legs behind to create a straight line from head to heels; 
3.Slowly lower your chest to the surface; 
4.Press upwards to start position.

1.Lie on the floor with both hands clasped, arms straight and overhead; 
2.Bring your upper body up and over while lifting your straightened legs until your hands and legs meet; 
3.Lower back to starting position.

1.Get to a basic lunge; 
2.With one foot ahead of the other, drop into a low lunge, bending both knees to 90 degrees; 
3.Then jump up switching feet in midair and drop into a low lunge on the other side.

1.Start in a full plank position; 
2.Lower your knees to the mat, keep the straight line from your head to your knees;
3.Then lower down, bending the elbows, and push up.

1.Lie on your back, bend in the right knee; 
2.Bring on the left leg off the ground and straighten it; 
3.Drive the hips upwards away from the floor, then return to the start position.

1.Lie on your back, bend in the left knee; 
2.Bring on the right leg off the ground and straighten it; 
3.Drive the hips upwards away from the floor, then return to the start position.

1.Start in plank position, keeping your legs straight; 
2.Bring one knee quickly into your chest and then back to plank; 
3.Quickly bring the opposite knee into your chest; 
4.Repeat.

1.From a plank position, bring one foot forward to the outside of right hand so you are in a low lunge position; 
2.Jump and switch feet in midair; 
3.Continue to alternate as quickly as possible.

1.Place your hands directly under shoulders in a push-up position; 
2.Use your glutes to stabilize your body; 
3.Keep your head in line with your back. Hold the position.

1.Start in a high plank position; 
2.Push through your palms and lift your hips into a downward dog; 
3.Return to high plank.

1.Lie on a mat with your hands under hips; 
2.Lift legs and bend knees to 90 degrees; 
3.Keep your knees bent and lift them close to your head; 
4.Slowly lower legs back to starting position.

1.Start in a seated position; 
2.Bring your palms to the ground, directly under shoulders; 
3.Lean back and then bridge your body upwards.

1.Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart; 
2.Raise arms out, parallel to floor; 
3.Quickly raise and lower arms within a controlled range.

1.Stand with hands on hips; 
2.Using only your glute muscle to lift your left leg to the side; 
3.Back to the start and repeat.

1.Stand with hands on hips; 
2.Using only your glute muscle to lift your right leg to the side; 
3.Back to the start and repeat.

1.Lie on your one side, your legs stacked and straight; 
2.Wrap your bottom arm in front of your torso; 
3.The other hand behind your head; 
4.Raise your torso and legs. Slowly return to start.

1.Lie on your right side, have your right arm support your head; 
2.Your left palm facing down on the mat; 
3.Bring your left leg up and down, in a slow, controlled manner.

1.Lie on your left side, have your left arm support your head; 
2.Your right palm facing down on the mat; 
3.Bring your right leg up and down, in a slow, controlled manner.

1.Start with high plank position; 
2.Rotate your body to left and balance on your right arm; 
3.Extend your right hand toward the ceiling. Hold the position.

1.Start with high plank position; 
2.Rotate your body to right and balance on your left arm; 
3.Extend your left hand toward the ceiling. Hold the position.

1.Stand with feet wider than hip width; 
2.Extend arms out in front of you; 
3.Lower your body toward the floor, bending your knees until they reach 90 degrees; 
4.Press back up to start position.

1.Lie on your stomach with arms and legs extended; 
2.Lift your arms and legs up toward the ceiling to form an "u" shape; 
3.Hold for seconds and lower back down.

1.Stand in front of a seat; 
2.Place hands on seat with fingers pointing forward; 
3.Bend arms and lower butt toward ground; 
4.Then straighten arms.

1.Place your elbows directly under shoulders; 
2.Keep body straight from head to toe; 
3.Push body up with one hand then the other; 
4.Lower down to one elbows then the other.

1.Stand with your back against the wall; 
2.Set your feet shoulder-width apart and 2 steps out from the wall; 
3.Gradually lower your back, bending legs until they’re in a 90 degree angle. Hold the position.

1.Lie on your stomach on a mat; 
2.Place your hands beside your chest; 
3.Keep your arms straight, while raising your torso off the floor. Hold the position.

1.Come onto your knees with your feet extended; 
2.Place hands at the base of your spine and open chest; 
3.Keep pressing thighs and hips forward as you slowly bend back.

1.Come onto all fours with your wrists under your shoulders and knees underneath your hips; 
2.Move your weight forwards looking up toward the ceiling; 
3.Move your weight backward tucking your chin into your chest.
